{"TopicId":224143,"ForumId":144,"TopicTitle":"Camera clipping distance is much too short in the flight camera. (shorter in flight than in the VAB)","CreatedByName":"Abelinoss","CreatedById":222638,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-03-16T23:33:56Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Abelinoss","CreatedById":222638,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-03-16T23:33:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.2.1 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 11 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0AMD Ryzen 5 5600 6-core Processor | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0NVIDEA GeForce RTX 3060 | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E15.91GB\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe camera clipping start distance is much higher in flight, than in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E. What does this mean? Well take a look at Shaun the Sheep here:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith a clipping start of 1 meter, we can see the entirety of his beautiful head.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00223BZV7ts.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022107.75\u0022 height=\u0022776\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/3BZV7ts.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nHowever, if we increase the clipping start distance, in this case to 2.7m (in KSP that increased clipping distance is the case during flight), we are suddenly exposed to the terrors of what\u0027s inside Shaun.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022JePhM8A.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022116.50\u0022 height=\u0022820\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/JePhM8A.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nArguably nobody wants to see that.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the same way the game does this. As a result you can not zoom in on things closely in flight properly. This is a shame when trying to make camera shots inside the cockpit, or close the the vehicle\u0027s body.\u003Cbr\u003E\nSee the attached image .zips for in game examples. I just found the Shaun the Sheep illustration to explain the problem better.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/applications/core/interface/file/cfield.php?storage=form_Fields\u0026amp;path=clippingbugimages1.zip\u0026amp;fileKey=%5B!AES128GCM%5BkQszXFXiNwbxxHKvBw%2B6DUu/Qx62Qq%2Br4oowfNSeYk83MRmvC3ZC0FcQ7cZaNjFltDAkFfjHAW8daIvfEk8BUTN7pQ4Axrs=%5D%5B3c29badc7c1d7fecbbb3011e%5D%5B5d8c49495881779a5cce16175debc852%5D%5D\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Eclippingbugimages1.zip\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/applications/core/interface/file/cfield.php?storage=form_Fields\u0026amp;path=clippingbugimages2.zip\u0026amp;fileKey=%5B!AES128GCM%5B%2BhqOOApN7atczUsJQKoFIiuLJFBmdv/8nirV3jz7Ze2tB